sections.heading: Repealed.
sections.text:
History:1978 Comp., § 32A-3-1, enacted by Laws 1993, ch. 77, § 62; repealed by Laws 2005, ch. 189, § 77.

Repeals.— Laws 2005, ch. 189, § 77 repealed 32A-3-1 NMSA 1978, as enacted by Laws 1993, ch. 77, § 62, the short title of the Family in Need of Services Act, effective June 17, 2005.

Compiler's notes.— Section 32A-3-1 NMSA 1978 was originally enacted as 32-3-1 NMSA 1978 by Laws 1993, ch. 77, § 62, but were recompiled to Chapter 32A NMSA 1978, in order to retain a historical link between the pre-July 1, 1993 law and the judicial precedents decided under that law. Citations to decisions under prior law have been included whenever possible.
